# POWERBACK Cursor Rules Index

This directory contains comprehensive cursor rules for the POWERBACK project. These rules guide AI assistants in understanding project patterns, conventions, and best practices.

## Rule Categories

### Architecture & Structure
- **01-project-structure.mdc** - Project organization, directory structure, file naming, module exports
- **02-react-components.mdc** - React component patterns, composition, lazy loading, performance
- **03-custom-hooks.mdc** - Custom hook patterns, state management, memoization
- **10-react-contexts.mdc** - React Context patterns, provider composition, dependency injection

### Styling & UI
- **04-css-styling.mdc** - CSS patterns, design system, Bootstrap integration, responsive design
- **24-css-class-naming.mdc** - CSS class/id naming: block--part-or-variant (BEM-like, single separator)
- **28-css-property-ordering.mdc** - CSS property ordering standard (referenced in specs)
- **29-bootstrap-css-blending.mdc** - Bootstrap + custom CSS blending patterns (referenced in specs)

### Backend Patterns
- **05-api-patterns.mdc** - API client patterns, route handlers, authentication, rate limiting
- **06-backend-services.mdc** - Service layer patterns, logging, database operations
- **12-models.mdc** - Mongoose model patterns, schemas, queries, indexes
- **13-controllers.mdc** - Controller patterns, error handling, logging, composition
- **14-authentication.mdc** - JWT authentication, token management, password handling

### Data & Validation
- **07-error-handling.mdc** - Error handling patterns, error types, error boundaries
- **08-validation.mdc** - Validation patterns, Joi schemas, form validation, compliance

### TypeScript & Types
- **09-typescript-patterns.mdc** - TypeScript patterns, interfaces, type guards, generics

### Quality & Testing
- **11-testing.mdc** - Testing patterns, Jest, React Testing Library, E2E tests

### Code Style & Conventions
- **15-naming-conventions.mdc** - Naming conventions for files, variables, functions, CSS
- **16-documentation.mdc** - Documentation patterns, JSDoc, comments, README structure
- **17-code-style.mdc** - Code style guidelines, formatting, best practices
- **23-commit-messages.mdc** - Commit message format: no double-quotes in title or body

### Specialized Rules
- **18-ai-assistant-guidelines.mdc** - AI assistant autonomy, permissions, and workflow
- **19-compliance-system.mdc** - FEC compliance system, tiers, limits, backend authority
- **20-client-storage.mdc** - Client storage policy, what can/cannot be stored
- **21-election-dates.mdc** - Election dates handling, snapshots, fallbacks
- **22-logging-telemetry.mdc** - Logging patterns, PII handling, central logger
- **26-copy-registry.mdc** - Copy text registry patterns (referenced in specs)

## How to Use These Rules

1. **Read Relevant Rules**: Review rules relevant to your task
2. **Follow Patterns**: Apply established patterns from the rules
3. **Maintain Consistency**: Keep code consistent with project conventions
4. **Update Rules**: Update rules when patterns evolve

